.TH "drm_gem_fb_create_handle" 9 "drm_gem_fb_create_handle" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_gem_fb_create_handle \- Create handle for GEM backed framebuffer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drm_gem_fb_create_handle
.BI "(struct drm_framebuffer *fb "  ","
.BI "struct drm_file *file "  ","
.BI "unsigned int *handle "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "fb" 12
Framebuffer
.IP "file" 12
DRM file to register the handle for
.IP "handle" 12
Pointer to return the created handle
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function creates a handle for the GEM object backing the framebuffer.
Drivers can use this as their \fIdrm_framebuffer_funcs->create_handle\fP
callback. The GETFB IOCTL calls into this callback.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success or a negative error code on failure.
